  "question_id": "51f40efe-6760-421f-b150-24c3bee7fbb6",
  "short_text": "Squares",
  "content": "Write a program to create a dictionary that contains keys as numbers from 1 to N and values are square of keys.<hr><b>Input</b><br/><br/>The input will be a single line containing an integer (N).<hr><b>Output</b><br/><br/>The output should be a single line containing the dictionary with key-value pairs from 1 to N.<hr><b>Explanation</b><br/><br/>For example, if the given N is 3, your code should print a dictionary with keys (1, 2, 3) and values (1, 4, 9). So the output should be<br/><pre style=\"font-family: Roboto Mono,Lucida Sans Typewriter,Lucida Console,monaco,Courrier,monospace;font-size: .85em;margin: 1.2em 0;\"><code style=\"font-family: Roboto Mono,Lucida Sans Typewriter,Lucida Console,monaco,Courrier,monospace;font-size: inherit;background-color: rgba(228, 237, 255,.5);border-radius: 0px;padding: 1em;display: block;-webkit-text-size-adjust: none;overflow-x: auto;white-space: pre;\">{1: 1, 2: 4, 3: 9}\n</code></pre>",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "HTML",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "077ae57b-7554-4c20-b179-b821702410fa",
      "code_content": "n = int(input())\n\nsquare_dict = {}\nfor num in range(1, n+1):\n    square_dict[num] = num*num\n\nprint(square_dict)\n",
      "language": "PYTHON39",
      "default_code": true
    }
